        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 16 at 5:28PM CDT until August 16 at 5:45PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Romeoville,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Clarendon Hills, Plainfield, Crest Hill, Orland Hills, Naperville,
Burr Ridge, Lisle, Orland Park, Aurora, Crystal Lawns, Willowbrook,
Westmont, Western Springs, Oswego, Indian Head Park, Hinsdale,
Darien, Woodridge, Downers Grove, Bolingbrook, Homer Glen, Palos
Park, Lemont, Willow Springs, and Countryside.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
